{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Notre-Dame Cathedral of Paris",
  "formatted_address": "6 Parvis Notre-Dame - Pl. Jean-Paul II, 75004 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.85296820000001,
    "lng": 2.3499021
  },
  "formatted_phone_number": "01 42 34 56 10",
  "website": "https://www.notredamedeparis.fr/",
  "rating": 4.7,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Happy Sunny",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115077109530605433852/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhrtA612fP6soH2c7PBaInHGNvnte3YNRS_qAs35pTYrJn3A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "Visiting the newly reopened Notre-Dame Cathedral was a dream come true! On this sunny Monday, I joined a well-organized queue that took about 20 minutes—well worth the wait (no need to buy tickets). The staff ensured a respectful atmosphere, requiring gentlemen to remove hats, dress neatly, and maintain silence, which added to the sacred ambiance.\nInside, the cathedral is nothing short of breathtaking. The restored beauty of the soaring arches, intricate stained glass, and serene orderliness left me in awe. Every detail radiates history, artistry, and spiritual grandeur. The experience was profoundly moving, evoking a deep sense of reverence and wonder. Notre-Dame is a true masterpiece, and I’m already looking forward to returning to bask in its timeless magnificence. Highly recommend this unforgettable visit to anyone!",
      "time": 1759791163,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Kristin Knowlton",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117007598821856439540/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhs5sqyk2pRq3TD1iMj_JBDKr0-K9rsVLzHgBU_CpIJC11KpM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "Long queue that moves quickly for free entrance. The stunning renovations make the cathedral look nearly new. Shockingly so. Gone are hundreds of years of candle smoke and soot. It is as if we are seeing it open for the first time as its original intent. I am glad I went but it truly makes me wish I’d seen it 10+ years ago to enjoy the patina of soot from dedicated parishioners. Truly something to visit and admire in quiet reverence.",
      "time": 1759838720,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Markie Kidd",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104346069599196752930/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaW-60ujYlnXRwIgCjkQFmY6ihb_Jw8336PLlPiwmFeD-AeX5s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 4,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "This is a beautiful place! I am sad the tickets were sold out and they only go up a couple days at a time, so I couldn't get any to go inside. I would've loved to see the cathedral and walk around. But the outside is still beautiful and noteworthy. Worth going just to see it. There's some boards with the history on it as well, so that was fun to read about.",
      "time": 1759497058,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Mena",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117562797607294797976/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIoFtLTQ4GuR66HujW21K4ec4MKf549jufMQW5A7kWd_iBhRYEzA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Notre-Dame Cathedral is absolutely breathtaking and truly a must-see in Paris. The architecture is stunning, with its incredible Gothic details, magnificent stained-glass windows, and the famous flying buttresses that make it one of the world’s most iconic landmarks. Even from the outside, the cathedral radiates history and beauty, but stepping inside feels like traveling back in time.\n\nThe interior is peaceful and awe-inspiring, with high vaulted ceilings and colorful light streaming through the rose windows. You can feel the weight of centuries of history, art, and spirituality in every corner. Climbing up to the towers is an unforgettable experience—seeing the gargoyles up close and taking in panoramic views of Paris is worth every step.\n\nDespite the damage from the 2019 fire, restoration efforts are ongoing, and it’s still one of the most moving and magical places to visit in Paris. Whether you’re interested in architecture, history, or just want to experience something truly iconic, Notre-Dame Cathedral is a place you’ll never forget.",
      "time": 1758873480,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "syria aziz",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108846232045255607050/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvrcEq_SjuBJTpjmkaFR9u_J7CekGxNeuCyzroq_0ShiQBHeo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Oh my dayz! I came to Paris in,April and unfortunately it was still closed. However on my stopover on tge way back to sunny England I had a coiple of hours to spare so decided to go. Am I glad I did, its beautiful. Typical Catholic, los of pomp and ceremony but its the little gems like the carvings and the 3d sculptures, how they managed to create such wonders! True masters of their trades. They are the ones who should be admired😍",
      "time": 1759229862,
      "translated": false
