{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Eiffel Tower",
  "formatted_address": "Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.85837009999999,
    "lng": 2.2944813
  },
  "website": "https://www.toureiffel.paris/fr",
  "rating": 4.7,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Aryan Patel",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108763739082590762673/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWN-HE_k5z5pJXS1qcI21MOWRQysPDimTv3SBv4uYyK53zGpc3LxQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "A Magical Day at the Eiffel Tower\n\nI visited the Eiffel Tower today and it absolutely lived up to the hype. From the moment I stepped onto the Champ de Mars, the Iron Lady’s latticework felt both grand and surprisingly graceful. The views from the top are breathtaking—Paris stretches out in every direction like a living postcard, with the Seine curving through the city and landmarks popping up everywhere you look.\n\nThe experience felt smooth and well-organized. Staff were friendly, and even with the crowds, the lines moved faster than I expected. I loved taking my time on each level—there’s something special about pausing with a coffee and just soaking in the panorama. As evening fell, the tower’s sparkle made the whole scene feel downright romantic and cinematic.\n\nIf you’re planning a visit, I’d recommend booking tickets ahead of time and going a bit before sunset so you catch daylight, golden hour, and the first twinkle after dark. Whether you take the elevator or brave the stairs, the journey itself is part of the fun.\n\nAll in all, today’s visit was unforgettable. The Eiffel Tower isn’t just a must-see—it’s a must-feel. Five stars! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️",
      "time": 1759495706,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Leena Gale",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106566144260087343783/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWNW8qef3UHdDzJEKwtH2kr9FMkkYjmiAJalqctMnbnrabg1UT=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "in the last week",
      "text": "Love it. Worth the 30 minute wait in the queue. Took the lift to the top. Fabulous views. Glass of champagne is 24euros. But you can keep the plastic glass as a souvenir. It's tapered so you can't put it down. Was crowded so you have to be patient but amazing visit and definitely as must whilst in Paris",
      "time": 1760130643,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "VIJAY Singh",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104142760539490840954/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFesP1izWpN2xPX9Rc8KA4_OqwkfVgly9yg9I_UD5sXs9xhqk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "4 weeks ago",
      "text": "Visiting the Eiffel Tower is an experience that truly lives up to its iconic reputation. From the moment you approach the base, the sheer scale and elegance of this iron masterpiece leave you in awe. Whether you’re a first-time visitor or returning, the view of the tower from the surrounding Champ de Mars and Trocadéro Gardens is breathtaking, offering perfect photo opportunities.\n\nThe structure itself is a marvel of engineering. As you ascend via the elevator or the stairs, each level provides a unique perspective of Paris. The panoramic views from the top are absolutely stunning—you can see the Seine River winding through the city, historic landmarks like Notre-Dame and Sacré-Cœur, and the charming rooftops of Paris stretching into the horizon.\n\nThe atmosphere around the Eiffel Tower is lively yet romantic. Street performers, souvenir shops, and cafes create a vibrant ambiance, while evening visits offer the unforgettable sight of the tower sparkling every hour on the hour. Dining at one of its restaurants is a special treat, combining fine cuisine with unparalleled views.\n\nTips for visitors: arrive early to avoid long lines, book tickets online if possible, and don’t forget your camera—every angle is Instagram-worthy. Whether you’re traveling solo, with friends, or on a romantic getaway, the Eiffel Tower offers a timeless experience that captures the heart of Paris. A visit here isn’t just sightseeing—it’s creating memories that will last a lifetime.\n\n⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Highly recommended for anyone visiting Paris!",
      "time": 1758172536,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Louie Farhat",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107211163946124799833/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWx3AGjQDuhM6RWEwIPYcIun6ilA8wfik6EbPnY69ugh5TviQ5I5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "I just had the most incredible experience at the Eiffel Tower with VIP access! Skipping the long lines made everything effortless, and I could fully enjoy every moment without feeling rushed. The elevator ride itself is amazing, giving you a sense of the tower’s grandeur as you rise above the city.\n\nOnce at the top, the views are absolutely breathtaking – the Seine winding through Paris, the Champs-Élysées stretching toward the Arc de Triomphe, and the city’s landmarks unfolding in every direction. Being able to linger, take photos, and simply soak in the atmosphere made the experience truly special.\n\nThe tower’s architecture is stunning up close, and from the observation decks, Paris feels alive, endless, and magical. VIP access made it all seamless and comfortable, turning an iconic visit into a relaxed, unforgettable adventure. This was one of the highlights of my trip – a breathtaking, once-in-a-lifetime experience I’ll never forget",
      "time": 1759413369,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Farnaz Arman",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105660369098718256151/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsThFDY1VBjmolKNP3ZkLoW6M7SgMdbi1tI7SUdSW5Q5yPOwW1=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Visiting the Eiffel Tower was such a fun experience! I loved how it sparkles for about 5 minutes on the hour, such a magical sight. We checked it out from a few different viewpoints and each one was amazing. The whole atmosphere was very lively and full of good vibes.\n\nA couple tips: I’ve heard there are lots of pickpockets in the area (though we didn’t experience any issues), so it’s good to stay aware. Definitely wear comfy shoes since there’s a lot of walking, and maybe grab a crepe or coffee while you’re there. I also saw people bringing wine and just sitting to enjoy the view, which looked like such a nice way to soak it all in.",
      "time": 1759212119,
      "translated": false
    }
  ],
