{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Louvre Museum",
  "formatted_address": "75001 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.8606111,
    "lng": 2.337644
  },
  "formatted_phone_number": "01 40 20 53 17",
  "website": "https://www.louvre.fr/",
  "rating": 4.7,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "M R",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108955353036896875224/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTu3lkygecgAvtACtXXBO6vvp2ZqzcBd_nHEL-uC2TMXS2hTy5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "The world knows the Louvre - and for good reason.  It's simply one of the greatest collections of artifacts ever brought together.  Every item has a story.  It would take days to go through it all, so I'd sincerely suggest a guide to maximize your time viewing the impressive collection.  If you can, plan your visit before or after summer, and avoid holidays.  I'd also suggest viewing the more iconic items close to closing time.  The crowds thin out and you'll have a better viewing experience.  Otherwise, try hard to be in the first group to enter and quickly go to the more popular items as quickly as possible.  Either way, have a plan.  Visit the museum's website and know what you want to see and where you need to go.  Absolutely buy tickets ahead of time.  There's stairs, escalators, lifts, and ramps to transit.  We walked 3 miles in just over 2 hours, so expect to walk - a lot.",
      "time": 1757814415,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Cassie Ishmael",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111496484144523819488/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOGafbaMzzYkcVpkpcbkjeN7qh8dxXIAsM7oIPOwOQeypRxWgN=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "Visiting the Louvre was an unforgettable experience. The art collection is incredible. Seeing the Mona Lisa, Venus de Milo and Winged Victory in person was surreal. The building itself is stunning and full of history.\n\nWith that being said, it was very crowded, people were everywhere. Especially around the Mona Lisa. I recommend planning ahead, picking a few must-see pieces and arriving early.\n\nOverall, visiting was absolutely worth it.  Just enter with realistic expectations. ❤️",
      "time": 1759508588,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Tates Napawan (Tates)",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104051659724326102869/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLH8ECM3kSDyZ8zMgu9iXQlLCfHXIYMwpFX8DIa2zN5DqHNwjaq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 months ago",
      "text": "We booked the Guide in advance in order to get in. Truly Iconic.\n\nMake sure you book early ahead of time.\n\nThe moment you walk through its grand entrance, you’re surrounded by centuries of masterpieces – from the Notorious Mona Lisa and Venus de Milo to Egyptian mummies and royal French artifacts.\n\nLHOOQ Mona Lisa try to say it in French real quick.\n\nThe museum itself is a work of art, with its elegant palace architecture and the striking glass pyramid in the courtyard.\n\nIt’s massive!! you could spend days exploring and still discover new rooms. My tip: plan your visit, wear comfortable shoes, and focus on a few sections you’re most interested in to avoid feeling overwhelmed.\n\nWhether you’re an art lover or just a curious traveler, the Louvre is an unmissable Paris experience. Every hallway tells a story, you would learn more if you had the tour guide explaining the history. Every priceless piece connects you to a moment in history.\n\nThe Visit, a walkthrough a thousand years of history, made us appreciate the evolution and intelligence of humankind.",
      "time": 1754765533,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Nubia Valenzuela",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113216488862536748216/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNOoW1mqpvE5U05o8k6GlmD5LZvjtDEXN0trS7vW2w5lBodN1fNA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 4,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "The most visited museum in the world, with encyclopedic collections spanning from Ancient Egypt to European painting. Seeing the Mona Lisa is iconic, though many, specificially me, every time, are surprised by its small size; and in my view some lesser-known works are even more impactful and finely executed. Overall, only the Hermitage in St. Petersburg, with its vast masterpieces, specifically painting, and imperial setting, surpasses it.",
      "time": 1759161793,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Paule Soffack",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102151215742276614255/reviews",
