{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Arc de Triomphe",
  "formatted_address": "Pl. Charles de Gaulle, 75008 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.8737917,
    "lng": 2.2950275
  },
  "formatted_phone_number": "01 55 37 73 77",
  "website": "https://www.paris-arc-de-triomphe.fr/",
  "rating": 4.7,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Louie Farhat",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107211163946124799833/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWx3AGjQDuhM6RWEwIPYcIun6ilA8wfik6EbPnY69ugh5TviQ5I5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "Visiting the Arc de Triomphe for the first time was truly amazing. Standing beneath this monumental arch, I could really feel the weight of history and the beauty of its design. Every carving and detail tells a story, and being there in person made me appreciate it so much more than just seeing it in pictures. Climbing the 284 steps to the top was a challenge, but absolutely worth it—the view of Paris stretched out in every direction, with the Eiffel Tower standing tall and the Champs-Élysées looking endless. The view was breathtaking and made the whole experience unforgettable. It’s one of those places that captures the magic of Paris in a single moment.",
      "time": 1759434243,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Louise Louise",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113889640493399732890/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQd26-zzhcHiQIo0tEUn_tGkNisnrHUoe41Nq97ocyXjT2RTg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "I visited the observatory in spring, summer, autumn and winter because the colours around the Arc de Triomphe change with each season, and they are beautiful. The view is also different by day and by night; while the Eiffel Tower offers a lovely panorama, the Champs-Élysées seen from here, especially at night, is even more striking and well worth the climb. Most people do not take the lift but climb the very narrow circular stone staircase, so those with mobility issues or the elderly should use the lift instead. Tickets must be purchased in advance for your preferred time slot on the official website. The staff at the ticket desk are very friendly, so if you need assistance, simply queue and they will be glad to help.",
      "time": 1759531541,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "souad yassine",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112625871040205065312/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYBLvCmema-OX39jHo26dFIjU2TnB34eFSzmdfiRnFg4I9c65w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "in the last week",
      "text": "Just visited the iconic Arc de Triomphe in Paris and I'm still pinching myself! This monumental arch was commissioned by Napoleon in 1806 to honor his Grande Armée and was finally completed in 1836. The monument's sheer grandeur and historical significance left me in awe. The views from the top are breathtaking, with the City of Light stretching out in every direction. The Tomb of the Unknown Soldier and the eternal flame add a poignant touch to this symbol of French national pride. A must-visit for anyone traveling to Paris!",
      "time": 1760256813,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Supreme intelligence Bureau",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103343165494891686519/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaDfSPfEypfMandFMxVHjH6XGBSrkMRj4Nicp9U8G8aSQeSao=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 3,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "The Arc de Triomphe is truly an iconic landmark with amazing architecture and history. But the surroundings could be managed much better. The area was overcrowded, and several food vendors seemed to overcharge or serve something different than promised, which felt disappointing. Also, too much noise around the site made it hard to enjoy the atmosphere peacefully. It’s worth visiting once, but the local management should take better care of maintaining the place’s charm and cultural vibe.",
      "time": 1759945161,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Gaurav Singal",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109967421851627726912/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURz87mDReQz4Yl8V9fscHGxykPH31YbxBn-DIVJwt1UUph49qf=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 4,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Of course, it’s worth visiting if you’re in Paris for the first time – the view from the top is truly impressive. Fortunately, the wait to go up isn’t usually too long. However, the area around the monument can be extremely crowded with tourists and heavy traffic, so crossing the streets requires caution. Also, be mindful of pickpockets. Still, as one of Paris’s most iconic landmarks, the Arc de Triomphe is undeniably beautiful and well worth a visit.",
      "time": 1759311450,
      "translated": false
    }
  ],
