{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Musée d'Orsay",
  "formatted_address": "Esplanade Valéry Giscard d'Estaing, 75007 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.8599614,
    "lng": 2.3265614
  },
  "formatted_phone_number": "01 40 49 48 14",
  "website": "https://www.musee-orsay.fr/fr",
  "rating": 4.8,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Alan YDR",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115118363143733544405/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUba_bhQU8VQoELhad-Iqhkcw24TOznz_hRdrm_ZoA_cBSX7U1a=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Probably my favorite museum in Paris. Good size with plenty to see yet not as overwhelming as Le Louvre. The main attraction is the 5th floor pieces by the impressionist masters (Claude Monèt, Cezanne, etc) lots of beautiful paintings. In addition they have a large collection of sculptures. Nice coffee shop in the lower level and a good size restaurant in the upper floor. Plan to spend a few hours wondering around and admiring the masterpieces.",
      "time": 1759041846,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "John Abrahamson",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110242012295636893027/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPtm3fAG__B1l-zrEC2Mc_m0ltuH2gRDllr7V0ydyWe-4EkFTy8A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "Nice collection of art. Very affordable/fair prices compared to many other museums and galleries. The collection wasn't as large as I imagined, especially being such a large building. But it's worth a visit. There are some great photo opportunities from above, and the impressionists art is fantastic.",
      "time": 1756931548,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Sivatharjini Sivarajasingam",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111973848578790989035/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMUmbX_Qu152VwNhcOuVHpxWVnOwVHEQH01FtSEY_Hvff9Iw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "This place is honestly incredible! Due to limited time I focused on my personal favourite - Impressionists but you could easily spend a whole day here. The building itself it stunning.\n\nWould recommend going out of peak season, I visited in August and it was very busy. I wonder how it would feel with less hustle and bustle.\n\nA memorable part of my trip to Paris!\n\nAlso there is a queue for tickets to be bought on the day. It was swift (5-10mins) and easy.",
      "time": 1758011025,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Gregory Cunniff",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105902971502176416007/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV787tTchFUbOcMm4CxEL0-1HCe8sQenixmLRDN1uF-AKAufMbS=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "3 weeks ago",
      "text": "V & I were lucky to be in Paris for three days on a stop over on our way home from our anniversary in Italy. I had not been to this museum in 25 years and it is everything I remembered and more.\n\nIf you like the French Impressionistic period this is your place. All the masters including Picasso, Van Gogh, Monet, Renoir, Cezanne, Manet, Seurat and the list goes on and on. And these are not the “also ran” pieces, the number of true masterpieces here is incredible in such a (relatively) small location. It’s not as grand or immense as the Louvre and not the wow factor of Monet’s largest works like in the l’Orangerie, but there are SO MANY masterpieces and with the right guide (Highly Recommended!), you will learn how the period evolved and who was involved and why they were involved and how they painted and where they painted and how it all came to be! There are few things in life as beautiful as art and to see these paintings IRL, it’s breathtaking.\n\nDon’t miss this beautiful place and its history and evolution because it more than just impressionist art. The sculptures are amazing - maybe not as mind blowing as Rome or Florence - but each as meaningful and amazing as the pieces you see elsewhere, and some you can’t see anywhere else.\n\nDon’t forget to invest in a guide. There are some great ones you can find in these reviews along with recommendations in certain very well known discussion forums that I have read (it) about.\n\nLast advice, avoid Tuesdays. The Louvre and l’Orangerie are closed in Tuesdays so this museum is poppin’ on Tuesdays. It is closed itself on Mondays like most every museum thus Wednesday and Thursday are likely the best time to visit.\n\nEnjoy!",
      "time": 1758692905,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Trouvaille B",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103591100681277977228/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhxHckC3MHsxSXPM93V-J07afnLSJ3TCkK6F63-F5UXEAGYpf7UQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "3 weeks ago",
      "text": "Free museum days are the first sunday id everything month and they require prior reservations, with no ability to secure a ticket the day of.\n\nWe made reservations and had a great visit. We spent about 2 hours here walking around. Highly recommend.\n\nThere is a small observation deck that will give a nice view of park of the city- there is also a restaurant there as well.",
      "time": 1758446999,
      "translated": false
    }
